# Data Model Conventions
#
# This file extends the base `.modscape/rules.md` with project-specific modeling rules.
# Rename to `rules.custom.md` to activate (remove the `.example` suffix).
# Rules defined here take PRIORITY over the base rules when they conflict.
#
# Read during: modeling sessions and the SDD design step.
# Scope: rules about the data model (YAML shape, table/column naming, schema constraints).
#        For SDD workflow and code generation rules, use modscape-spec.custom.md instead.
#
# Delete or comment out any section you don't need to customize.

## Naming Conventions

# Table ID naming rules:
# - Fact tables:      fct_<event>            e.g., fct_orders
# - Dimension tables: dim_<entity>           e.g., dim_customers
# - Mart tables:      mart_<domain>_<metric> e.g., mart_sales_revenue
# - Staging tables:   stg_<source>_<entity>  e.g., stg_salesforce_accounts

## Allowed Table Types

# Uncomment to restrict which conceptual.kind values are permitted:
# - This project only uses `fact`, `dimension`, and `mart`.
# - Do NOT use `hub`, `link`, or `satellite`.

## Domain Topology

# Uncomment to define the fixed domain structure:
# - This project has the following domains: <domain1>, <domain2>, <domain3>
# - Every new table MUST be assigned to one of these domains.

## Required Columns

# Uncomment to enforce mandatory columns per table kind:
# - All fact tables MUST include: id, created_at, updated_at
# - All dimension tables MUST include: id, is_deleted

## SCD Policy

# Uncomment to set the SCD policy for dimension tables:
# - Dimension tables use SCD Type 1 only. Do NOT apply scd.type: type2 or higher.

## Tags Policy

# Uncomment to require BEAM* tags on specific table kinds:
# - All fact tables MUST have at least one of: WHAT, HOW_MUCH, COUNT
# - All dimension tables MUST have at least one of: WHO, WHERE, WHEN
